post_text:
The Greene County Board of Education has approved a revised academic calendar for the 2020-2021 school year. This new calendar includes:
- A later start date for students on August 17th to allow more time for parents to make plans for the upcoming school year;
- Front-loaded professional learning days so staff can participate in professional learning on developing their distance-learning teaching skills;
- Three week-long Intersessions to provide for preview of upcoming learning and review and remediation of previous learning.

